<div class="mdui-typo"><h1 id="upset-vt">upset <strong><em>vt</em></strong></h1>
<p>英 /ʌp'set/    美 /ʌp'set/  </p>
<p>(upset, upset)</p>
<h2 id="_1">释义</h2>
<h4 id="1">1.<strong>弄翻；打翻：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>upset a bowl of soup 
打翻一碗汤</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>The life boat was upset by the waves.
救生船被大浪打翻了。</p></div>

<h4 id="2">2.<strong>打乱；搅乱 (计划、安排等)：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>He arrived an hour late and upset our plan. 
他迟到了一个小时，打乱了我们的计划。</p></div>

<h4 id="3">3.★ <strong>使生气；使心烦意乱</strong></h4>
<p>to make sb worry or feel unhappy：</p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>This decision is likely to upset a lot of people. 
这项决定很可能会使许多人不快。</p></div>

<h4 id="4">4.<strong>使 (肠胃) 不适</strong></h4>
<h2 id="_2">派生词汇</h2>
<p>upsetting /ʌp'setɪŋ/ adj   </p></div>